South Africa Narrows Gap With Russia’s Palladium Production

-- B y   N i c h o l a s   L a r k i n
-- 
2011-05-05T15:10:55Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-05/south-africa-narrows-gap-with-russia-s-palladium-production.html
South Africa  increased palladium
production by 7 percent last year, narrowing the gap between its
output and that of Russia, the biggest producer, according to
researcher GFMS Ltd.  South Africa’s mine supply was 2.65 million ounces in 2010,
the London-based researcher said in a report published today.
Russia’s output rose 2 percent to 2.72 million ounces, GFMS
said.  The U.S. remained the third-biggest supplier, even as
production declined 8 percent to 374,000 ounces, while  Canada ’s
output climbed 26 percent to 352,000 ounces, the researcher
said. Zimbabwe, the fifth-biggest miner, increased supply by 26
percent to 222,000 ounces, GFMS said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nicholas Larkin in London at 
 nlarkin1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
